rgin-bottom: 40px;"></div>\n<a href=" http://avada.theme-fusion.com/purple-custard-customer-spotlight/ " class="short-btn  large square "  target="_blank">   View The Customer Spotlight </a>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theme-fusion.com/avada-customer-spotlight-purple-custard-2/">Avada Customer Spotlight: Purple Custard</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theme-fusion.com">Theme Fusion</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:72:"https://theme-fusion.com/avada-customer-spotlight-purple-custard-2/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"3";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:54:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:59:"4 Key Benefits of Using a Premium WordPress Theme Framework";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:68:"https://theme-fusion.com/benefits-using-premium-wordpress-framework/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:77:"https://theme-fusion.com/benefits-using-premium-wordpress-framework/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 03 May 2016 17:04:35 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"Avada";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"Beginners Guide";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"New Site";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"WordPress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"theme framework";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:33:"http://theme-fusion.com/?p=397243";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:594:"<p>If you are are serious about creating a WordPress website, youve likely run across the dilemma of whether or not to stick with free themes or go with a full-fledged premium solution such as a single-purpose theme or framework. In order to understand whether or not you should make the jump to a premium framework, [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theme-fusion.com/benefits-using-premium-wordpress-framework/">4 Key Benefits of Using a Premium WordPress Theme Framework</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theme-fusion.com">Theme Fusion</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"Tom Ewer";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9525:"<p>If you are are serious about creating a WordPress website, youve likely run across the dilemma of whether or not to stick with free themes or go with a full-fledged premium solution such as a single-purpose theme or framework.</p>\n<p><span id="more-397243"></span></p>\n<p>In order to understand whether or not you should make the jump to a premium framework, you must first understand what a framework is and what the biggest benefits of using one are.</p>\n<p>Are you ready to get a grip on the key benefits of a premium framework? In this post, youll learn what aspects make a premium framework valuable, and whether or not you feel its the right choice for you.</p>\n<h2>What Is a Premium WordPress Framework?</h2>\n<p>There are two definitions of a WordPress framework, depending on who the framework is designed for:</p>\n<div class="shortcode-list">\n<ol>\n<li>A <em>developers</em> framework is designed as a platform upon which WordPress developers can build their own child themes.</li>\n<li>A <em>non-developers</em> framework enables users to build deeply functional and diverse websites without having to touch a line of code. They consolidate incredible power into a flexible central theme and plugin combination.</li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n<p>In this post, we will explore the latter, compared to what you might receive for a free, <a href="http://www.freemium.org/what-is-freemium-2/" target="_blank">freemium</a>, or more limited single purpose premium WordPress themes.</p>\n<h2>Benefit #1: Full Support With Better Staffing</h2>\n<figure><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-397250" src="http://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/premium-framework-support.png" alt="Premium Framework Support" width="1018" height="337" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/premium-framework-support.png 1018w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/premium-framework-support-300x99.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 1018px) 100vw, 1018px" /></figure>\n<p>Popular premium frameworks typically offer full support administered by an appropriately sized staff to make sure your problems get solved as quickly as possible.</p>\n<p>Being able to access better support and a staff whose job it is to make sure your products work the way you expect them to will save you endless hours of frustration and wasted time trying to fix problems by yourself.</p>\n<h2>Benefit #2: Features Youll Never See (But Still Benefit From)</h2>\n<figure><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-397248" src="http://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/premium-framework-backend-features.png" alt="Premium Framework backend updates" width="750" height="471" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/premium-framework-backend-features.png 750w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/premium-framework-backend-features-300x188.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px" /></figure>\n<p>Theres a lot that goes into building a fully featured WordPress framework!</p>\n<p>WordPress itself sets <a href="https://make.wordpress.org/core/handbook/best-practices/coding-standards/" target="_blank">certain standards</a> and is always implementing new features. A premium framework stays on top of these standards while taking advantage of what behind-the-scenes features are available to make your website work quickly and efficiently.</p>\n<p>A few features you may not notice include:</p>\n<div class="shortcode-list">\n<ul>\n<li>Flawless compatibilitywith a wide range of plugins</li>\n<li>Optimization for speed and SEO</li>\n<li>&#8216;True&#8217; responsiveness (i.e.flawlessly implemented across the gamut of devices)</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h2>Benefit #3: Regular and Reliable Updates to the Framework</h2>\n<figure><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-397251" src="http://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/premium-framework-updates-1024x611.png" alt="Premium framework updates" width="1024" height="611" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/premium-framework-updates-1024x611.png 1024w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/premium-framework-updates-300x179.png 300w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/premium-framework-updates.png 1062w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>\n<p>Due to better staffing, your framework will have more regular and reliable updates; not only to keep the engine running as smoothly as possible, but to introduce new features and implement important changes to improve your experience.</p>\n<p>This will keep your site more secure, stable, and powerful while also ensuring that your ongoing and ever-changing needs are being addressed by the framework for the long term.</p>\n<h2>Benefit #4: All of Your Functionality Is in One Place</h2>\n<figure><a href="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/premium-framework-grouped-interface.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-403372"><img src="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/premium-framework-grouped-interface.jpg" alt="premium-framework-grouped-interface" width="650" height="449" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-403372" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/premium-framework-grouped-interface.jpg 650w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/premium-framework-grouped-interface-300x207.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px" /></a></figure>\n<p>When using a framework, the core functionality you need is already included. In other words, you can easily mold your website into whatever it needs to be without needing to install a number ofplugins to handle SEO best practices, drag-and-drop page building, shortcodes, sliders, optimized media embeds, and the like.</p>\n<p>This means spending less time researching, installingandmanaging additional plugins just to cover the needs of your website. A framework is built to flexibly handle any situation while reducing the amount of work youll need to put in. Not to mention, all of this built-in functionality receives the same support, care, and updates that you&#8217;re used to.</p>\n<p>Compared to single-purpose premium themes, this is where frameworks really count for the money.</p>\n<p>Single-purpose themes may come with theme-level features, but a framework will come with everything you need to build a completewebsite right out of the box. This includes being able to drastically change the look and feel of the final product!</p>\n<h2>The Pros and Cons of Free and Single-Purpose Premium Themes</h2>\n<p>Even when you understand all the benefits of a premium framework, its always good to evaluate your options. In this case, the alternatives are free themes and single-purpose premium themes. Weve broken down some of the important pros and cons of these alternatives for your own analyzation.</p>\n<h3>Free Themes: Pros</h3>\n<div class="shortcode-list">\n<ul>\n<li>Cost no money (up front)</li>\n<li>Some free support from the WordPress community</li>\n<li>May offer one or two strengths</li>\n<li>Work well with a plethora of plugins</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h3>Free Themes: Cons</h3>\n<div class="shortcode-list">\n<ul>\n<li>Can cost time and moneyin bug-fixing and customization</li>\n<li>Lack of solid support framework</li>\n<li>The back end code is sometimes (often?)not maintainedin the long term</li>\n<li>Does not offer as wide a range of features and customizability as premium frameworks</li>\n<li>Requires the extensive use of alternative plugins for any of your desired features</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h3>Single-Purpose Premium Themes: Pros</h3>\n<div class="shortcode-list">\n<ul>\n<li>Better theme functionality than free themes</li>\n<li>More reliable support</li>\n<li>Regular and reliable updates</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h3>Single-Purpose Premium Themes: Cons</h3>\n<div class="shortcode-list">\n<ul>\n<li>Does not include plugin functionality</li>\n<li>Often costs the same as a premium framework, without all of the same features</li>\n<li>Is only designed for one type of user</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\n<p>When building a WordPress website, you are faced with a choice: Sticking with free themes because of the low-cost entry, or deciding whether to step it up a notch and go with a premium framework. However, this can be a difficult choice when you dont know whether a premium framework is going to benefit you in the right ways.</p>\n<p>If you are looking to save money over the lifespan of your website, you may find that a premium framework is for you. This is due to the fact that premium frameworks:</p>\n<div class="shortcode-list">\n<ol>\n<li>offer better support than free themes,</li>\n<li>have more regular and reliable updates to a variety of important features, and</li>\n<li>includeall the functionality you need in one place.</li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n<p>Not all premium frameworks offer these features, so you should inspect the product and company before buying. Of course, we have based these standards on <a href="http://theme-fusion.com/avada/" target="_blank">our own premium framework, Avada</a>.</p>\n<p>Are you ready to take the plunge? Are you already on a premium framework such as Avada? Let us know how you feel about premium frameworks in the comments!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theme-fusion.com/benefits-using-premium-wordpress-framework/">4 Key Benefits of Using a Premium WordPress Theme Framework</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theme-fusion.com">Theme Fusion</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"https://theme-fusion.com/benefits-using-premium-wordpress-framework/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"8";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s